==English==

===Proper Noun===
'''Aras an Uachtaran'''
#The official residence of the Irish [[president]], situated in Phoenix Park in Dublin.

===Etymology===
#([[Irish]]) From [[w:Áras an Uachtaráin|Áras an Uachtaráin]], literally ''The hall of the president''.
===Usage Note===
# Basically the same term is used in both Irish and English, however, the Irish form includes the stroke over the first and last letter 'A'.
===Pronunciation===
ar us / an  / uct er awn
